        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2016-02-22 00:03:34.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nIt would be better if http://review.whamcloud.com/18436 landed in preference to the ext4-large-eas.patch fix here, because that one is clear from the commit log that there is a fix included, and not just an update to the latest kernel.\n\nI won't shed a tear if this one lands and mine does not, but in general it is better to be clear in your patch commit message and summary what the patch is changing, otherwise it can cause difficulty in the future (e.g. skipping patches for backporting to maintenance branches because this one \"only\" updates to RHEL 7.2 3.10.0-327.10.1 kernel and there is a later one that updates to 3.10.0-456.20.2 or whatever).",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
